----

**SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES:** Following the events of Addendum 7000.2, SCP-7000-α has been successfully neutralized and SCP-7000 has been divided into SCP-7000-A and SCP-7000-B. All survivors of SCP-7000-α are to be tracked, found, and brought into the Foundation's custody to receive necessary treatments.

Otherwise, the containment of SCP-7000 is to be centered around the dissemination of misinformation to the public, no matter the current status of modern society. The SCP Foundation is to be represented as a non-governmental organization dedicated to the protection of humanity, and a plausible excuse or cover story is to be developed and scattered across the remnants of society.

----

**DESCRIPTION:** SCP-7000 is the former designation given to an essophysical manifestation, formerly located within the Kuiper Belt and currently orbiting nearby Neptune. It originally took the form of a binary asteroid that measured approximately 10 km in diameter.

Due to the poorly understood nature of SCP-7000, the anomaly was believed to be the manifestation of luck or probability, as it had varied effects within the entirety of the Solar System and, presumably, other object masses within its gargantuan range of effect.

SCP-7000-α is the name given to a quasi-catastrophic event that affected the Solar System from 2029 to 2034, caused by the impact of an unidentified object with SCP-7000. As SCP-7000 was believed to be a manifestation of luck itself and its mass was demonstrated to be relatively small within the Kuiper Belt, it was assumed that unlikely or "unlucky" events would continuously occur within its range of effect.

This was shown to be the cause of SCP-7000-α, which later unleashed a series of catastrophic events[[footnote]]See Addendum 7000.1 for more information.[[/footnote]] and almost destroyed the entirety of Earth and its Moon, among other celestial bodies within the Sol System.

----

**FINAL TRANSMISSION:** On the morning of April 15th, 2034, a series of Foundation drones controlled by Foundation AI Binary Star arrived at SCP-7000 via the use of probes. Though most drones were heavily damaged by SCP-7000's effects, the rest were able to establish physical contact with the anomaly and clean the remaining debris off in the following 59 hours. Upon finishing, the drones planted a series of remote explosives in the center of SCP-7000, splitting the asteroid into SCP-7000-A and SCP-7000-B.

All drones were heavily damaged. This led Binary Star to generate a transmission in morse code, which later resulted in most of its data being sent to Lunar Site-32. This took approximately 3 days to arrive.

----

**AFTERMATH:** SCP-7000's aftermath and the status of humanity are currently unknown. A backup of Binary Star has been activated by Lunar Site-32's staff and is actively inspecting Foundation facilities in hopes of locating any survivors.

SCP-7000 is pending reclassification to Ticonderoga. All files pertaining to the SCP-7000 research project have been archived by order of Lunar Site-32's Department of Para-Astronomy, and this document has been reduced to Level 1 Clearance.

